M||tx|---
M||titl|Do not wrap a simple expression w/ a primitive result tp in useMemo
M||impa|lo-md
M||impa|wasted computation on every render
M||tags|rerender, useMemo, op
M||tx|---
M|Do n|tx|When an expression is simple (few logical or arithmetical operators) and has a primitive result tp (boolean, number, string), do not wrap it in `useMemo`.
M|Do n|tx|Calling `useMemo` and comparing hook dependencies may consume more resources than the expression itself.
M|Do n|**In|**
M|Do n|tx|```tsx
M|Do n|func|Props) {
M|Do n|tx|const isLoading = useMemo(() => {
M|Do n|tx|return us.isLoading \|\| notifications.isLoading
M|Do n|tx|}, [us.isLoading, notifications.isLoading])
M|Do n|tx|if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />
M|Do n|tx|// return some markup
M|Do n|tx|}
M|Do n|tx|```
M|Do n|**Co|**
M|Do n|tx|```tsx
M|Do n|func|Props) {
M|Do n|tx|const isLoading = us.isLoading \|\| notifications.isLoading
M|Do n|tx|if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />
M|Do n|tx|// return some markup
M|Do n|tx|}
M|Do n|tx|```